Oooh how i love that...devils play...

Anyways, nothing really exciting has happened....yet.  Surrounded by a couple new friends, from which i am learning a lot of and love to hang out with.  Life has been nice to me so far, and i continue on the road to success.  

Who knew that the one thing i didnt wanna do in the first place, would be what i would be doing...and am enjoying:-P  Being a nurse is pretty cool, i mean ive worked in the medical field a lot and well im learning more, and right now im trying to get my degree as a registered nurse, and then move to boston, where i will receive my bach. in nursing and get into becoming an O.R. Nurse.  Things are going pretty smoothly and i'm crossing my fingers that things will continue to go the same.  

On another subject, I'd like to say that i really miss my old friends from OHS.  i havent seen anyone from Orange for quiet a while and am wondering how and what theyre up to.  Hopefully safe, and in good health with their lives going according to planned :-)  Ever since i rid myself of aol, i havent seen much of anyone lately.  Jaime i hope youre doing well, and that your dreams are coming true for you.  remember not to let anyone put you down :-) Hope all of your relationships are doing well and i hope to see you soon so we can hang out and you can tell me what youve been up to :-)  

Luis i havent seen you in a while and hope the best for you and your gf :-) I also hope your dreams are coming true and maybe ill stop by your work or house for a quick hello :-) Take care.

I've emailed everyone else whom does not visit or have livejournal, take care ya'll :-P

I've been getting myself into trouble lately :-P but have also been able to bail myself out....and am grateful :-)

School so far is going well...working on my career and all.  So far, i have to say that i am loving life.  Meeting new people, and making new friends, life just seems to be moving and i like it.  

That's about all i have to say for right now...nothing too new :-) take care ppls

In my life i have had friendships that felt like they would last a life time, and i have had friendships in which the trust and bond between two good friends was broken.  And im aware that in my life, i may continue to have a little of each world.  Sometimes though, its unexpected.  friends in which you rely on can easily turn on your back and it can sometimes sting pretty bad.  As is the case with Selina.  

I write this in my journal because i want to share this with friends and would like to express my feelings over this whole subject. Also, to get a few things cleared up, which i think is most important, and hopefully those reading this will respect me and my thoughts for it.  

The way things began, at least in my perspective, is when in high school, im unsure of whether it was my junior yr or senior yr, i commented to Selina (Quintana.. as you guys should know) about Stephanie Pounder.  Im not sure where we were going but i knew that stephanie was invited...i made somewhat of a cringe and selina asked me why the cringe.  I told her that i didnt know steph very well, but from what it seemed like, she was always mad or at least seemed like it, or frusterated. As all of you know, when going out with friends and someone is a little down or mad or whatever, it kinda kills the moment.  At least for me it does, because if i know someone isnt enjoying themselves its kind of a downer.  I told selina how i cant really say much because i dont know her as well as her or jaime did, but that it always seemed like she was in a bad mood, which  made it no fun.  

Years pass by, and while in college i took a photo class, and stephanie happened to be in it.  I actually thought it was nice because i hadnt seen people from high school much other than close friends, and it was nice to see someone familiar.  Getting to know stephanie a lot better, i commented to selina on how she isnt what i thought she was and isnt at all moody or whatever.  But on the other hand, shes nice and was fun to talk with and work with while in photo class.  I'm not sure when or how what i had said years ago came up between selina and steph, but it seems that selina changed my words, saying that i disliked, hated, or was annoyed by steph.  Either way, stephanie took this info and ran with it.  Later, she reacted with disgust towards me and didnt seem to even want me in the same room, and i of course did not understand why.  After asking selina, already having a suspicion that she might have said something, and she confirmed that she mentioned "something" about it.  Selina told me that stephanie was asking about whether ppl liked her and studff like that, and selina happned to mention what i thought.  Whether that is true or false, im not sure.   

Later on, speaking to Jaime, he imed a message stating that he heard i didnt like stephanie.  After talking to him about it, i found out that Stephanie herself had ran with the info Selina gave and complained about it to jaime.  Ever since then, their has been hostility between me and stephanie.  
Hostility that sometimes caused Selina some pain in the butt. Selina sometimes having to lie either to me or stephanie about things.  When i would hang out with selina, she would lie to stephanie about her where abouts and stuff like that, which is really Selinas decision and her own personal stuff.  

I decided that i wasnt going to let any of this bother  me, and let it go.  Yet over time, i have found it irrritating because it was a problem that was never resolved. 

Another thing that bothered me was the fact that this "selina" has seemed to turn her back on me, at least thats the way i feel.  Selina was starting to ignore me, not return calls and eventually disappeared from my life until a few days ago, when i called her to say hello.  I dont know about you, but when your close friends with someone, you dont just disappear for no reason and not state way.  When i can, i email, im, or call friends at least to say hi for a few secs, and if i dont stay long its because i have a hectic schedule.  So when selina stopped calling or anything, i took it to the heart because we had hung out for so long and she was my friend in which i confided in.   I would have understood if she was sick, or something like that, but by the look of things it just seems that she stopped caring and is hanging out with stephanie a lot more.  Whether steph has somehow had an influence on this i dont know. 

What i do know is that, im trying to rid myself of people who really are no good and trying to clear things up as well.  I ask an apology to Jiame, Mike and other friends whom i have spoken to and have told me over and over again that a friend such as selina is a waste of time and effort.  Also, id like to say that i have never said anything about disliking stephanie or anything before, and whatever selina has said is a lie.  But, learning how things are, id like to say that Stephanie too, is a waste of time.  

NOW, i do not like her at all, and have found that she, just as selina, creates drama in her life because she has nothing else better to do with her time.  

If stephanie ever had a chance to read this, id like to say this to her:
Whatever Selina has told you about me not liking you, is a lie.  Yet your reaction to the things she has said make me realize that you are truly a waste of time.  In photo class, i was always nice to you, respectful, and i always tried to help you out when you needed the help.  Never did i treat you or act in a way that could hint that i disliked you or hated you.  In fact, i grew to like you.  And it amazes me how fast you have forgotten that, just because Selina poisoned my words and changed them into things i never said about you.  I dont like you now, nor will i ever, and the reason for that is because of the way you handled this whole situation.  You ran with the info she gave you and whined about it to ppl.  Never once asking yourself if it could be true, or even confronting me about it.  Youre a coward and thats all i have to say to you.  

To Selina:
I'd like to tell you that i really thought you and i were good friends, but your actions over this whole time has proven otherwise.  You lied about me, and lied to my face when i confronted you about the whole situation with stephanie.  You did not even try to clear things up, in fact it seemed that you were rather pleased with her and i not liking each other.  Jaime was right when he told me that a friend like you, was a waste of my time and that you truly were not my friend.  You love drama in your life, and by the looks of it so does steph and i am so over high school and am moving on with my life, so my advice to you is to GROW UP. 

Thats all i have to say for right now, and please feel free to comment on any of this.  Thanks.

I read an article today about some parents, in florida (the crazy state :-P) that went on strike.  They moved out of their house and live on the front porch. Why? because theyre fed up with their children not doing their chores.  So, theyre on strike.  Dishes have piled up, clothes unwashed, no cooking - jsut tv dinners.  I say good for them, the kids are 17, and 13 and still refuse to do them.  I thought that was pretty funny....

There ar so many things ive put off, just procrastinating about any sort of thing i have to do and i really should start to finish them off.  Presents to finish wrapping, cards to send, all that stuff.  Finals to study for, my room to clean, clothes to wash, ughhhhh.  I just hide in my bed and hope for it to al go away.  Ive never been so lazy before...i dunno how i got this way but im feeling more and more of a failure.....im crazy :(  I'll go clean my room when i get home, ill prob feel better when my room isnt so cluttered.  Maybe ill post a pic of what my room looks like now....and Jaime...now it really is BAD...not like the time u teased about :-P

Ok now....close your eyes and think of the one place you would love to be at this very very very moment.  It's crucial that all your senses be involved in this so think of a smell that might be there (perfume? trees? all that), think of the things you would see, feel, hear, and taste. I'm not sure how i feel right now...
I am contemplating everything in life, like most people my age do every single day, and i dont feel sad and i dont feel happy.  I feel alright, and i guess as long as im feeling alright, everything is alright.  But its not, cuz at the same time, stuff sucks ass.  
Anywho.... i went to class today and we watched a movie about discrimination.  It was actually pretty cool cuz there was a teacher who taught a third grade class, and she wanted them to feel first hand, what it was like to have someone discriminate against you.  Maybe you guys have heard about it?  Its called "A Class Divided" and its pretty darn cool.  The day after Martin Luther King Jr. was assasinated, this teacher thought that it was time someone teach kids that discrimination is a bad thing to do, and she didnt want them to just hear her talk, but to have them experience it themselves and see what others feel.  So she divided her class into two groups, people with blue eyes and people with brown eyes.  She told the browned kids that those with blue eyes were better than those with brown eyes, therefore they get better treatment.  The blue eyed kids were allowed 5 minutes more for recess and a whole bunch of other stuff.  Eventually, the brown eyed kids came to feel resentment towards those with blue eyes, and those with blue eyes felt more powerful.  The class that was once joyful and playful with one another, now came to somewhat hate those who werent seen at their level.  A fight even arose because one boy called another boy "brown eyed".  Then the next day the teacher said that she had made a mistake and those with brown eyes are actually superior to those with blue eyes, and so things turned around and now those with blue eyes were treated like crap i guess, and they felt resentment just like those who did the day before.  In the end, the kids learned to understand that disciminating is no fun, and all were friends once again.  The kids said they hated the feeling of being an outcast and didnt like it.  The teacher told them if they would ever discriminate another person and they said no because it didnt feel good.  14 yrs later they had a reunion and they all said how much it affected their lives and so on....it was pretty cool...wish our teachers would do that today.  Anywho...thats all :)  I talk too much.....

Finally on spring break! Sad that its only a week though...wish it was longeerrrr.  I permed my hair yestaday and i like it, im very happy with it.  I really want to dye my hair, but im a lil afraid that its going to really damage my hair and that would suck butt.  So i guess i'll have to wait....ugh...waiting.  Isn't Johnny Depp to die for?

I try keeping myself together....but i feel like im losing a grip on things around me.  
Psychology is so hard.  I do enjoy going to psych class but i have to admit that it stresses me out.  So many things to learn and understand, not that i dont enjoy it, its just so overwhelming.
